 {"id":"bd-2u0","title":"Integrate ConsoleConfig into Server builder API","description":"## Purpose and Rationale

Wire ConsoleConfig into FastMCP Server so users can configure all console features through the server builder. This is the final integration point that makes everything accessible.

## Background

All the rich_rust features need to be controllable through the Server API. Users should be able to configure console behavior when building their server, either by passing a config directly or through individual builder methods.

## Technical Specification

### Server Integration

```rust
// crates/fastmcp/src/server.rs

use fastmcp_console::{
    ConsoleConfig, FastMcpConsole, FastMcpTheme, DisplayContext,
    BannerStyle, TrafficVerbosity,
};

impl Server {
    // Existing fields plus:
    console_config: ConsoleConfig,
    console: Option<FastMcpConsole>,

    pub fn new(name: &str) -> Self {
        Self {
            name: name.to_string(),
            // ... existing fields
            console_config: ConsoleConfig::from_env(),
            console: None,
        }
    }

    /// Set complete console configuration
    pub fn with_console_config(mut self, config: ConsoleConfig) -> Self {
        self.console_config = config;
        self
    }

    /// Set console theme
    pub fn with_theme(mut self, theme: FastMcpTheme) -> Self {
        self.console_config.theme = theme;
        self
    }

    /// Configure banner style
    pub fn with_banner(mut self, style: BannerStyle) -> Self {
        self.console_config = self.console_config.with_banner(style);
        self
    }

    /// Disable startup banner
    pub fn without_banner(mut self) -> Self {
        self.console_config = self.console_config.without_banner();
        self
    }

    /// Enable request/response traffic logging
    pub fn with_traffic_logging(mut self, verbosity: TrafficVerbosity) -> Self {
        self.console_config = self.console_config.with_traffic(verbosity);
        self
    }

    /// Enable periodic statistics display
    pub fn with_periodic_stats(mut self, interval_secs: u64) -> Self {
        self.console_config = self.console_config.with_periodic_stats(interval_secs);
        self
    }

    /// Force plain text output (no colors/styling)
    pub fn plain_mode(mut self) -> Self {
        self.console_config = self.console_config.plain_mode();
        self
    }

    /// Get the initialized console
    fn console(&self) -> &FastMcpConsole {
        self.console.as_ref().expect("Console not initialized")
    }

    /// Initialize console from config
    fn init_console(&mut self) {
        let context = self.console_config.resolve_context();
        self.console = Some(FastMcpConsole::new_with_theme(
            self.console_config.theme.clone(),
            context,
        ));
    }
}
```

### Updated run_stdio

```rust
impl Server {
    pub async fn run_stdio(mut self) -> Result<(), Error> {
        // Initialize console
        self.init_console();

        // Initialize rich logging
        if let Some(level) = self.console_config.log_level {
            self.init_rich_logging(level)?;
        }

        // Display startup banner
        if self.console_config.show_banner {
            self.display_startup_banner();
        }

        // Display capabilities summary
        if self.console_config.show_capabilities {
            self.display_capabilities_summary();
        }

        // Start periodic stats if enabled
        if self.console_config.show_stats_periodic {
            self.spawn_stats_logger(
                Duration::from_secs(self.console_config.stats_interval_secs)
            );
        }

        // ... rest of run_stdio implementation
    }
}
