### Usage Examples

```rust
// Example 1: Full configuration
use fastmcp::Server;
use fastmcp_console::{ConsoleConfig, BannerStyle, TrafficVerbosity};

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    let config = ConsoleConfig::new()
        .with_banner(BannerStyle::Full)
        .with_log_level(tracing::Level::DEBUG)
        .with_traffic(TrafficVerbosity::Summary)
        .with_periodic_stats(30);

    Server::new("my-mcp-server")
        .with_console_config(config)
        .tool(calculate)
        .run_stdio()
        .await
        .unwrap();
}

// Example 2: Builder methods
Server::new("my-mcp-server")
    .with_banner(BannerStyle::Compact)
    .with_traffic_logging(TrafficVerbosity::Headers)
    .plain_mode() // For CI/testing
    .run_stdio()
    .await
    .unwrap();

// Example 3: Environment-driven (production)
Server::new("my-mcp-server")
    // ConsoleConfig::from_env() is default
    .tool(my_tool)
    .run_stdio()
    .await
    .unwrap();
```

### Documentation Updates

Add to README.md:

```markdown
## Console Configuration

FastMCP provides rich console output for debugging and monitoring.

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `FASTMCP_BANNER` | Banner style: full/compact/minimal/none |
| `FASTMCP_LOG` | Log level: trace/debug/info/warn/error |
| `FASTMCP_TRAFFIC` | Traffic logging: none/summary/headers/full |
| `NO_COLOR` | Disable all colors |

### Programmatic Configuration

\`\`\`rust
use fastmcp_console::{ConsoleConfig, BannerStyle};

let server = Server::new("demo")
    .with_console_config(
        ConsoleConfig::new()
            .with_banner(BannerStyle::Compact)
    );
\`\`\`
```

## Implementation Steps

1. Add ConsoleConfig field to Server struct
2. Initialize console in run_stdio()
3. Add all builder methods to Server
4. Wire banner display to config
5. Wire traffic logging to config
6. Wire periodic stats to config
7. Update examples in repo
8. Update README with configuration docs

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] with_console_config() accepts full config
- [ ] Individual builder methods work correctly
- [ ] Environment variables control behavior
- [ ] Banner respects configuration
- [ ] Traffic logging respects verbosity setting
- [ ] Periodic stats work when enabled
- [ ] plain_mode() disables all styling
- [ ] Examples compile and work

## Testing Strategy

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_server_console_config() {
    let config = ConsoleConfig::new()
        .without_banner()
        .plain_mode();

    let server = Server::new("test")
        .with_console_config(config);

    // Verify config is applied
    assert!(!server.console_config.show_banner);
    assert!(server.console_config.force_plain);
}
```

